!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

describe /dɪˈskraɪb/

(describing,described,describes) 

1. V-T If you describe a person, object, event, or situation, you say what they are like or what happened. 描述 

例： We asked her to describe what kind of things she did in her spare time. 我们请她描述她在闲暇时做些什么。 

例： She read a poem by Carver which describes their life together. 她读了一首卡弗描写他们在一起生活的诗。 

2. V-T If a person describes someone or something as a particular thing, he or she believes that they are that thing and says so. 讲成; 称作 

例： He described it as an extraordinarily tangled and complicated tale. 他把它讲成了一个格外错综复杂的故事。 

例： Even his closest allies describe him as forceful, aggressive, and determined. 甚至他最亲密的同盟者们都说他强势、好斗且坚决。

</div>

